  <file id="933" original="/csunplugged/topics/content/en/error-detection-and-correction/programming-challenges/detect-parity-error-in-any-rows/scratch-hints.md" source-language="en" target-language="en-UD" datatype="plaintext">
    <body>
      <trans-unit id="10364" identifier="e5a8f351cb3831de4956ee4e298b286f">
        <source>Make a variable called “number of rows” and set its value to the input
entered by the end user.</source>
        <target>crwdns10364:0crwdne10364:0</target>
        <note>Context: XPath: /ul/li/p</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="10365" identifier="7083f866baf445000e3bae4c81255fb4">
        <source>Make a variable called “black cards total” and set its value to 0.</source>
        <target>crwdns10365:0crwdne10365:0</target>
        <note>Context: XPath: /ul/li/p</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="10366" identifier="2ed1cd5c0e3d0dde08b7b041d6766996">
        <source>Also make a string variable called “row” and set its value to the input
entered by the end user.</source>
        <target>crwdns10366:0crwdne10366:0</target>
        <note>Context: XPath: /ul/li/p</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="10367" identifier="2f4a23bb331b49deab57bcfa5facbcb5">
        <source>Check each letter of the string and if it’s ‘B’ add 1 to the “black
cards total”.</source>
        <target>crwdns10367:0crwdne10367:0</target>
        <note>Context: XPath: /ul/li/p</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="10368" identifier="9553a95985f33fa1f859eba48ac0b344">
        <source>If the value of the “black cards total” is even (after checking every
card in the row), display a message that the parity row is ok.</source>
        <target>crwdns10368:0crwdne10368:0</target>
        <note>Context: XPath: /ul/li/p</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="10369" identifier="df23d0fc7343d44a737987653a9e0efc">
        <source>If the value of the “black cards total” is odd, display a message that
the row has a parity error.</source>
        <target>crwdns10369:0crwdne10369:0</target>
        <note>Context: XPath: /ul/li/p</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="10370" identifier="99c28c176db15abc91d1017412e507c0">
        <source>Repeat this “number of rows” times (for each row).</source>
        <target>crwdns10370:0crwdne10370:0</target>
        <note>Context: XPath: /ul/li/p</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="10371" identifier="f33d46db20b024d4b72d2e7e3943f53d">
        <source>You can access a letter at the specified position in a string by using
the &lt;code&gt;scratch:letter (1) of [world]&lt;/code&gt; block under “Operators”.</source>
        <target>crwdns10371:0[world]crwdne10371:0</target>
        <note>Context: XPath: /ul/li[2]/p</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="10372" identifier="b3f38b5bce22059c78a7498b774ea904">
        <source>For example: &lt;code&gt;scratch:letter (1) of [world] //w&lt;/code&gt;</source>
        <target>crwdns10372:0[world]crwdne10372:0</target>
        <note>Context: XPath: /ul/li[2]/p</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="10373" identifier="f05bc4fbd37b9a919535e0bfacb00f76">
        <source>In this challenge you need to access all the letters in user’s input
(each row of the parity trick) and check to see how many of them
are equal to B (black).</source>
        <target>crwdns10373:0crwdne10373:0</target>
        <note>Context: XPath: /ul/li[3]/p</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="10374" identifier="919f1cfeadc417110703fa378b505c8a">
        <source>Store the total number of black squares in a variable called “black
cards total”.</source>
        <target>crwdns10374:0crwdne10374:0</target>
        <note>Context: XPath: /ul/li[3]/p</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="10375" identifier="4c8b5356652b84eab1850e4166a0d5fa">
        <source>You can find how many letters a string has by using the
&lt;code&gt;scratch:length of [world]&lt;/code&gt; block unders “Operators”.</source>
        <target>crwdns10375:0[world]crwdne10375:0</target>
        <note>Context: Paragraph text&#13;
XPath: /ul/li[4]/p</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="10376" identifier="74b149e3b36f1e579074bdc00ee459a7">
        <source>To find out if a number is even or odd, use the &lt;code&gt;scratch:() mod ()&lt;/code&gt; block
(under &quot;Operators&quot;) to find the remainder after dividing that number by
two.</source>
        <target>crwdns10376:0crwdne10376:0</target>
        <note>Context: XPath: /ul/li[5]/p</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="10377" identifier="2f8afc38cafe1c4e222387f03bd8cafe">
        <source>If the remainder is zero the number is even.</source>
        <target>crwdns10377:0crwdne10377:0</target>
        <note>Context: XPath: /ul/li[5]/p</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="10378" identifier="93f1d0c9d19c520c234d5439590b9ffa">
        <source>For example: &lt;code&gt;scratch:(37) mod (10) //7&lt;/code&gt;</source>
        <target>crwdns10378:0crwdne10378:0</target>
        <note>Context: XPath: /ul/li[5]/p</note>
      </trans-unit>
    </body>
